<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-76-0493 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper reports on the development of a natural evaporative coolerfor residential buildings in a hot arid climate. The testing was doneat the Wind Tunnel Laboratory of Building Science Department at U.S.C.The wind tunnel was employed to simulate the inside and outside temperaturedifferential for different sizes of natural evaporative cooler. Temperaturedifferentials of 30{sup 0}F were achieved.</TEXT></DOC>